import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['open'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['open'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['open'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Opening Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of opening prices?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['open'], label='Opening Price')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['close'], label='Closing Price')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between opening and closing prices?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['ret'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['ret'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['ret'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Return on Investment')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of returns on investment?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['signal'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color=['red', 'green', 'blue'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of signals?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Signal')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
